Package asap.realizer.pegboard

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AfterPeg
    AfterPegs define TimePegs that remains at a minimum time offset from a 'regular' TimePeg.
    that is: afterPeg.getGlobalTime() >= linkedPeg.getGlobalTime()+offset if the link's value is TimePeg.VALUE_UNKNOWN, it is ignored.
    BeforePeg
    BeforePegs define TimePegs that remains at a minimum time offset before a 'regular' TimePeg.
    that is: beforePeg.getGlobalTime() <= linkedPeg.getGlobalTime()+offset if the link's value is TimePeg.VALUE_UNKNOWN, it is ignored.
    BehaviorCluster
    Stores cluster of connected behaviors
    BehaviorKey
    behaviorId, bmlId pair
    BMLBlockPeg
    Peg that refers to the absolute time of the start of BMLBlock with id id.
    OffsetPeg
    OffsetPegs define TimePegs that remains at a fixed time offset from a 'regular' TimePeg.
    PegBoard
    Keeps track of TimePegs and BMLBlockPegs
    PegKey
    Stores sync point information, e.g.
    TimePeg
    BML SynchronisationPoint, used in the realizer as intermediate, slightly flexible timing structure.
